# Lingua Franca (Codecademy)

## Overview

The Lingua Franca project is a command-line exercise designed to practice fundamental Linux filesystem navigation, file management, text processing, and shell operations.

I completed this project within a Xubuntu virtual machine rather than using the in-browser terminal to gain additional experience working in a Linux environment.

---

## Objectives

Practice using common Linux commands to:

- Navigate the filesystem
- Create and manage files and directories
- Copy and move files
- Delete files and directories
- Work with wildcards
- Redirect command output
- Use pipes to combine commands
- Search and manipulate text
- Configure shell environment settings

---

