## Reflection

The most valuable part of this project was not learning individual commands, but learning how multiple commands can be combined to solve practical problems.

The task involving `wc`, `grep`, pipes, and output redirection required significantly more problem-solving than the earlier tasks and provided the strongest learning opportunity in the project.

Completing the project without consulting the solution helped reinforce my understanding of command-line workflows and increased my confidence working in a Linux environment.
